{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Under new rules to be issued by the White House, federal agents can still consider race and ethnicity when stopping people at airports and immigration checkpoints, officials said.", "abstract": "Obama administration is set to issue new rules curtailing use of profiling, but new policies will be exempt for national security and border investigations and will not apply at airports, border crossings or immigration checkpoints; new categories to be prohibited along with race are religion, national origin, gender, sexual orientation and gender identity.", "section_name": "U.S.", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Matt", "role": "reported", "lastname": "APUZZO", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}, {"lastname": "SCHMIDT", "rank": 2, "firstname": "Michael", "role": "reported", "organization": "", "middlename": "S."}], "original": "By MATT APUZZO and MICHAEL S. SCHMIDT", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/06/us/politics/obama-to-impose-racial-profiling-curbs-with-exceptions.html", "lead_paragraph": "Under new rules to be issued by the White House, federal agents can still consider race and ethnicity when stopping people at airports and immigration checkpoints, officials said.", "headline": {"main": "U.S. to Continue Racial, Ethnic Profiling in Border Policy", "print_headline": "U.S. to Continue Racial Profiling in Border Policy"}, "_id": "54825b8138f0d8403d9cc1cf", "word_count": "1203", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/12/06/us/PROFILE/PROFILE-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/12/06/us/PROFILE/PROFILE-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2014/12/06/us/PROFILE/PROFILE-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/12/06/us/PROFILE/PROFILE-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "wi